devdoc.details: Contract that provides an NFT mining process that creates an NFT.  And based on the likes of the contract the initial supply of the NFT decreases. This contract inherites ERC721UTIStorage and Ownable contracts from Openzeppelin.

constructor.details: Initialzes the NFT by giving name and symbol and sets the maximum number of mintable nfts and the price.

currentSupply().details: a function tha returns the number of the nfts that have been minted.

returns._0: uint256 the number of the nfts that have been minted.

getLikes().details: getter function that returns the number of likes stored in the state variable _likes

getMaxMintable().details: getter function that returns the number of the nfts that can be minted

getPrice().details: getteer function that returns the price of the nfts

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

purchase().details: a payable function that transfer the money from the buyer to the owner of the nft. The buyer receives the nft.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: a function that changes the base uri of the nft. This function can be called inly from the owner of the contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateState(uint256).details: A function that updates the state variables based on the difference of current likes and previous likes of the image. When the likes increases the number of the nfts that can be minted decreases. Moreover the price of the nft increaces by 1. If likes decreases no transaction can be completed.

params.likes: the number of the reactions retrieved by the api and passed through the javascript inyp the smart contract.
